City of The Joy Wellness Resort

City of the Joy is a visionary project dedicated to creating a harmonious and sustainable way of life. It embraces a serene environment, health, and a peaceful life by promoting natural food that nourishes both the body and mind. Rooted in the belief that nature provides everything we need, this project ensures that future generations benefit from the best that nature has to offer. The fresh air, organic produce, and holistic lifestyle help in preventing and even curing long-term illnesses through nature’s healing power. City of the Joy is a place where nature itself becomes the provider of food, health, and well-being, ensuring a pure and fulfilling life for all who embrace it.

The Inspiration

The idea for City of the Joy emerged from a deep desire to create a space where people can live in sync with nature while healing and growing. Inspired by age-old Indian wellness philosophies and modern eco-living concepts, the project provides a holistic approach to life.

FAQ's

What is the City of Joy by Sampangi Infra?


City of Joy is a luxury wellness resort and real estate project near Hyderabad, offering fully managed holiday homes within a serene, eco-friendly environment. It combines sustainable living with modern comforts, providing residents access to wellness therapies, organic farming, and nature-centric amenities.

Where is the City of Joy located?

The City of Joy is situated in Aliar near Hyderabad, Telangana, India. Its strategic location offers easy accessibility to major highways and urban centers, making it an ideal choice for those seeking a tranquil yet connected lifestyle.

What types of properties are available at City of Joy?


City of Joy offers elegant 500 sq. ft. designer holiday homes nestled on spacious 201 sq. yard plots. These homes are part of a fully developed wellness resort, providing a perfect blend of luxury and nature.

What amenities are included in the City of Joy wellness resort?


Residents of City of Joy enjoy access to world-class wellness amenities, including yoga zones, herbal gardens, spa therapies, organic living spaces, and a fully equipped gymnasium. The resort also offers therapies like acupuncture, hydrotherapy, and reflexology.

Is the City of Joy project legally approved?

Yes, City of Joy is both DTCP and RERA approved, ensuring clear titles and legal documentation. This provides buyers with confidence in the legitimacy and compliance of the project.

How can I schedule a site visit to City of Joy?
To schedule a site visit, you can contact Sampangi Infra at +91 96422 47777 or email info@sampangiinfra.com. We offer free site visits to help you experience the tranquil environment and amenities firsthand.

    Sampangi Partners with IIT Tirupati

    It is with great enthusiasm that we share the news of a ground breaking collaboration between IIT-Tirupathi and Sampangi Infra for our bio-farming initiatives. The Heads of Department have consented to furnish geo-tagging data for the agricultural plots, along with detailed layouts of the irrigation channels and the water management infrastructure. This collaboration marks a significant achievement for Sampangi Infra, as it stands as the first company of its kind to join forces with an IIT institution to enhance farming methodologies.
    The partnership between IIT-Tirupathi and Sampangi Infra is poised to set a new standard in bio-farming practices. The primary objectives include the integration of advanced geo-tagging technology for precise mapping of agricultural plots, which will enhance the monitoring and management of crop growth. Additionally, the partnership aims to develop sophisticated irrigation channels and water management systems, ensuring optimal resource utilisation and sustainability. This initiative is expected to serve as a model for future agricultural collaborations, promoting eco-friendly farming techniques that can lead to increased crop yields, improved quality of produce, and a boost in the economic well-being of the farming community. By leveraging the academic prowess of IIT-Tirupathi and the innovative spirit of Sampangi Infra, the project aspires to revolutionise the agricultural sector, making it more technologically advanced, environmentally sustainable, and economically viable. This collaboration is not just a milestone for Sampangi Infra, but a leap forward for the entire bio-farming industry in India.
